      "creatureType": "",
      "blurb": "Skeleton cavalier commander",
      "publicNotes": "<h3>Conversion notes (this module)</h3><p><strong>Role:</strong> Scarwall's eternal watch commander — Lord of the causeway gate (B1), riding out with twelve skeletal champions when intruders reach the bridge's midpoint. He remembers only fragments of life; the causeway is all that's left. <strong>The bloodless way:</strong> his <strong>gold locket</strong> lies in his old office (B8, @Check[type:perception|dc:33]) — a portrait of a beautiful woman and an inscription begging her Lashton to remember her and come home safe. If a PC carries it, <em>he senses it and halts the charge</em>, demanding its immediate return; handed the locket, he gazes at the portrait for one round, then crumbles to dust. His skeletons and mount still attack — but the commander himself need never be fought.</p>",
      "privateNotes": ""
    },
